en_654401_0	Major General Kumar Jayapathirana, General Officer Commanding (GOC), 21 Division with the intention of further promoting welfare facilities for soldiers took steps to put up a utility building in the 21 Division premises, comprised of a library, saloon, beauty culture centre, tailor shop and a cobbler station.
en_654401_1	The opening of the new facility took place on 28 July in the presence of the GOC gracing as the Chief Guest.
en_654401_2	212 Brigade troops supported the construction work of this utility complex under the supervision of the 212 Brigade Commander.
en_654401_3	This new facility complex at the 21 Division Headquarters was a long-felt need of the soldiers and was the result of an initiative taken by the 21 Division GOC.
